Name: Currency
Notes: Identifies currency used for price.

Name: IOIOthSvc
Notes: No longer used

Name: Rule80A
Notes: Also known as OrderCapacity

Name: SecurityID
Notes: Unique instrument ID as qualified by the exchange per tag 22-SecurityIDSource.

Name: SendingDate
Notes: No longer used

Name: TotNoOrders
Notes: Formerly named ListNoOrds

Name: NoDlvyInst
Notes: No longer used

Name: DlvyInst
Notes: No longer used

Name: SecurityDesc
Notes: Instrument Name.

Name: SettlCurrency
Notes: Identifies currency used for settlement price.

Name: CxlType
Notes: No longer used

Name: MaturityMonthYear
Notes: Format YYYYMM (i.e. 200912)

Name: ContractMultiplier
Notes: Number of deliverable units per instrument, e.g., peak days in maturity month or number of calendar days in maturity month.

Name: MarketDepth
Notes: Identifies the depth of book.

Name: UnderlyingIDSource
Notes: This value is always '8' for CME.

Name: UnderlyingSecurityID
Notes: Unique instrument ID as qualified by the exchange per tag 305-UnderlyingSecurityIDSource.

Name: UnderlyingSymbol
Notes: Underlying security's Symbol.

Name: NoSecurityAltID
Notes: This tag is under development.

Name: SecurityAltID
Notes: This tag is under development.

Name: SecurityAltIDSource
Notes: This tag is under development.

Name: CFICode
Notes: Indicates the type of security using ISO 10962 standard, Classification of Financial Instruments (CFI code) values. See: http://www.cmegroup.com/confluence/display/EPICSANDBOX/Market+Data+-+CFICode+Table+of+Values

Name: UnderlyingProduct
Notes: Product complex (2=Commodity/Agriculture, 4=Currency, 5=Equity, 12=Other, 14=Interest Rate, 15=FX Cash, 16=Energy, 17=Metals)

Name: NoLegs
Notes: Number of legs.

Name: LegCurrency
Notes: Currency for this leg.

Name: MinTradeVol
Notes: The minimum trading volume for a security.

Name: LegPrice
Notes: Price for the futures leg of a covered.

Name: LegSymbol
Notes: Only sent for options strategies and futures spreads.

Name: LegSecurityID
Notes: Unique instrument ID for the leg.

Name: LegSecurityIDSource
Notes: Identifies source of tag 602-LegSecurityID value. This value is always '8' for CME.

Name: LegCFICode
Notes: CFI code for this leg.

Name: LegMaturityMonthYear
Notes: Leg's MaturityMonthYear.

Name: LegStrikePrice
Notes: Strike price of the leg.

Name: LegSecurityExchange
Notes: Security exchange of the leg.

Name: LegSecurityDesc
Notes: Leg security description (e.g., ESM0 C1130)

Name: LegRatioQty
Notes: The ratio of quantity for this individual leg relative to the entire multi-leg instrument.

Name: LegSide
Notes: 1=Buy, 2=Sell.

Name: NoUnderlyings
Notes: Number of underlying instruments.

Name: SettlPriceType
Notes: Indicates whether settlement price is preliminary or final (1=Final, 2=Theoretical, 100=Actual preliminary for instruments not subject to rounding, 101=Actual preliminary for instruments subject to rounding).

Name: SecuritySubType
Notes: Indicates Strategy type.

Name: LegSecuritySubType
Notes: If leg repeating group is a spread, the strategy type for the spread.

Name: LastUpdateTime
Notes: Timestamp of when the instrument was deleted.

Name: ExpirationCycle
Notes: Indicates if the instrument expires at the trading session close, or at a specified last eligible trade date. If '0', the instrument is eligible for Day orders only. If '2', the instrument is eligible for GTC/GTD orders (outrights only).

Name: NoEvents
Notes: Number of repeating EventType entries.

Name: EventType
Notes: Code to represent the type of event (5=Activation, 7=Last eligible trade date)

Name: EventDate
Notes: Date of event.

Name: NbInstAttrib
Notes: Number of repeating group InstrAttribType entries.

Name: InstAttribType
Notes: Tag 871-InstAttribType and tag 872-InstAttribValue function together where tag 871 indicates the type of value that the following tag 872 will contain.

Name: InstAttribValue
Notes: Tag 871-InstAttribType and tag 872-InstAttribValue function together where tag 871 indicates the type of value that the following tag 872 will contain.

Name: TotNumReports
Notes: Total number of reports returned in response to a request.

Name: LegStrikeCurrency
Notes: Currency of the strike price of the leg.

Name: StrikeCurrency
Notes: Currency in which the strike price is denominated.

Name: MinPriceIncrement
Notes: Minimum constant tick for the instrument, sent only if instrument is non-VTT (Variable Tick table) eligible.

Name: SecurityUpdateAction
Notes: M=Modify, D=Delete.

Name: UnitOfMeasure
Notes: Unit of measure for the products' original contract size.

Name: LegOptionDelta
Notes: Delta used to calculate the quantity of futures used to cover the option or option strategy.

Name: MDFeedType
Notes: Describes a class of service for a given data feed.

Name: LotType
Notes: The quantity type used for the leg of the spread. This tag is required to interpret the value in tag 1231-MinLotSize.

Name: MaxTradeVol
Notes: The maximum trading volume for a security.

Name: NoMdFeedTypes
Notes: Number of repeating FeedType repeating group entries.

Name: MatchingAlgorithm
Notes: Matching algorithm (F=FIFO, K=Configurable, C=Pro-Rata, A=Allocation, T=FIFO with LLM, O=Threshold Pro-Rata, S=FIFO with TOP and LLM, Q=Threshold Pro-Rata with LLM, Y=Eurodollar options)

Name: MaxPriceVariation
Notes: Differential value for price banding.

Name: ImpliedMarketIndicator
Notes: Informs the market that an instrument is eligible for implied trading (Implied In & Out; 0=Non-implied, 3=Implied). If this tag is not present, instrument is non-implied.

Name: EventTime
Notes: Time of event.

Name: MinPriceIncrementAmount
Notes: Under development.

Name: UnitOfMeasureQty
Notes: This field contains the contract size for each instrument (in combination with tag 996).

Name: LowLimitPrice
Notes: Lower price threshold for the instrument. Orders submitted with prices below the lower limit will be rejected.

Name: HighLimitPrice
Notes: Upper price threshold for the instrument. Orders submitted with prices above the upper limit will be rejected.

Name: TradingReferencePrice
Notes: The most recent settlement price.

Name: SecurityGroup
Notes: Product code.

Name: AppIID
Notes: The channel ID as defined in the XML Configuration file.

Name: NoLotTypeRules
Notes: Number of quantity types in the upcoming repeating group.

Name: MarketSegmentID
Notes: Identifies the market segment.

Name: ContractMultiplierUnit
Notes: Indicates the type of multiplier being applied to the product. Used in combination with tag 231. 1=Hour, 2=Day

Name: FlowScheduleType
Notes: The schedule according to which the electricity is delivered in a physical contract, or priced in a financial contract.

Name: PriceRatio
Notes: Used for price calculation in spread and leg pricing.

Name: ClearedVolume
Notes: Indicates the total cleared volume of instruments traded during the prior trading session.

Name: OpenInterestQty
Notes: Indicates the total open interest for the market at the close of the prior trading session.

Name: LegSecurityGroup
Notes: Product code for this leg.

Name: TradingReferenceDate
Notes: Indicates the date the last update to the settlement price.

Name: DecayQty
Notes: Indicates the quantity that a contract will decay daily by once the decay start date is reached.

Name: DecayStartDate
Notes: Indicates the date at which a decay contract will begin to decay.

Name: OriginalContractSize
Notes: Fixed contract value assigned to a product.

Name: UserDefinedInstrument
Notes: Y=User defined, N=Not.

Name: DisplayFactor
Notes: Contains the multiplier to convert the CME Globex display price to the conventional price.

Name: MinCabPrice
Notes: Defines cabinet price for outright options products.

Name: PricingModel
Notes: Identifies options pricing model (F=Fischer-Black, W=Whaley).
